    {
      "title": "Setup Instagram CLI",
      "description": "https://github.com/supreme-gg-gg/instagram-cli\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-07 17:22)\nNow the setup is complete. The CLI is installed, the skill is documented, and TOOLS.md is updated. The only thing left is authentication, which requires the user to do interactively.\n\n---\n\n**Instagram CLI is installed and ready** (v1.4.4, via npm `@i7m/instagram-cli`).\n\nHere's what was already in place and what I finished up:\n\n- **Binary**: `/opt/homebrew/bin/instagram-cli` -- already installed globally\n- **Config**: `~/.instagram-cli/config.ts.yaml` -- set up with compact chat layout, ASCII image rendering\n- **Skill docs**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/instagram-cli/SKILL.md` -- full usage reference already written\n- **TOOLS.md**: Added instagram-cli entry so Uni knows it's available\n\n**One thing you need to do manually**: Log in. Run:\n\n```\ninstagram-cli auth login --username <your_instagram_username>\n```\n\nIt'll prompt for your password and 2FA code if you have it enabled. This is interactive so I can't do it for you -- Instagram needs the real credentials flow. Once logged in, the session is stored locally and you can use all the features:\n\n- `instagram-cli chat` -- list DM threads\n- `instagram-cli chat -u <username>` -- open a specific DM\n- `instagram-cli feed` -- browse your feed in the terminal\n- `instagram-cli stories` -- view stories\n- `instagram-cli notify` -- check notifications\n\nNo Mission Control page needed here -- this is a terminal tool, not something with data to dashboard. No cron jobs either. Just authenticate and you're good to go.",
      "labels": [
        "skill",
        "instagram"
      ],
      "priority": "High",
      "column": "review",
      "order": 3,
      "_id": "card_1772854523572",
      "createdAt": 1772854523572,
      "updatedAt": 1773352388579,
      "executorStatus": "completed"
    },
