      "_id": "card_1772902763886",
      "title": "[Passive Income] Notion Template Empire - Copy & Improve Top Sellers",
      "description": "Next Task. Get one good Template\n\n1. Scrape the Notion template marketplace and Gumroad for top-selling templates:\n   - Categories: project management, habit trackers, budgets, content calendars, CRM, job search\n   - Record: title, price, reviews, estimated sales, features list\n2. For the top 20 sellers, create improved versions:\n   - Better visual design (more polished layout, color schemes)\n   - Add 2-3 features competitors lack\n   - Write compelling descriptions and setup guides\n   - Price 30-50% below competitors\n3. Generate template files using Notion API or export-ready format\n4. Create Gumroad product listings with:\n   - Preview images (screenshots of template)\n   - Detailed feature comparison vs competitors\n   - Setup documentation PDF\n5. Build Mission Control dashboard at /app/notion-templates:\n   - Track: templates created, views, sales, revenue per template\n   - Competitor price tracker (monitor their prices weekly)\n   - Ideas queue for next templates to build\n6. Set up weekly cron: scan marketplace for trending new categories\n7. Store all template source files in ~/.openclaw/workspace/projects/notion-templates/\n\n---\nCONTEXT\n- Startup budget: $0 (Gumroad is free to list)\n- Manual steps (user must do): Upload templates to Gumroad/Notion marketplace, set pricing, occasionally respond to customer questions\n- Source idea: idea_1709856002_nt01\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-08 07:57)\ne infrastructure — a passive income project for selling Notion templates on Gumroad.\n\n**What was created:**\n\n**6 detailed template source files** (`~/.openclaw/workspace/projects/notion-templates/templates/`) — each with full Notion database schemas including properties, formulas, relations, rollups, multiple views, and color schemes:\n1. Project Command Center ($19) — time tracking, risk register, client portal\n2. Habit Forge ($12) — habit stacking, streak recovery, identity alignment\n3. Money Mind ($15) — multi-currency, investments, debt snowball, net worth\n4. Content Engine ($19) — AI prompts, repurposing workflow, hashtag lab\n5. Deal Flow ($19) — lead scoring, revenue forecasting, follow-up cadence\n6. Career Launch ($12) — salary negotiation toolkit, skills gap, offer comparison\n\nAll priced 30-70% below competitors (avg $16 vs competitor avg $33).\n\n**Market research** — 20 competitors analyzed with pricing, features, weaknesses, and estimated sales. Plus web research stored in `research/`.\n\n**Marketing assets** — Gumroad product listings with compelling copy, feature comparison charts, and setup documentation in `docs/`.\n\n**Mission Control dashboard** at `/app/notion-templates` — stats cards, templates table with status tracking, competitor tracker, ideas queue (5 future templates), and category breakdown. Nav item added at top of sidebar.\n\n**Weekly cron job** — marketplace scanner runs every Monday 6am SGT, searches for trending categories and price changes via Tavily, sends Telegram notification. Registered in `jobs.json`.\n\n**What you need to do manually:**\n- Recreate the templates in Notion using the JSON schemas as blueprints (each file has exact property definitions, formula strings, and view configurations)\n- Create a free Gumroad account and list templates using the descriptions in `docs/gumroad-listings.json`\n- Take screenshots for preview images\n- Update template statuses in `data.json` from \"draft\" to \"live\" as you publish — the dashboard tracks it all",
