    {
      "_id": "card_1773247957620",
      "title": "[Passive Income] AI Gaming Clan Logo & Banner Generator",
      "description": "Build and deploy: Automated service creating custom logos, banners, and branding assets for gaming clans, esports teams, and streamers. Uses AI to generate designs based on game type, team name, and color preferences.\n\n---\nCONTEXT\n- Startup budget: 50\n- Manual steps (user must do): Set up payment processing, create design templates, monitor customer feedback\n- Source idea: idea_1773182900348_0\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-12 04:40)\naw/workspace/agents/gaming-logo-gen/` with solid code. I verified and completed all the integration pieces.\n- **Web server** is live on `http://localhost:3847` as a persistent launchd service (`ai.openclaw.clanforge`). It serves a polished dark-themed landing page with an order form, pricing cards, and a generation API.\n- **Mission Control dashboard** at `/app/clanforge` shows order stats, revenue, breakdowns by style/game/type, recent orders table, pricing info, and quick reference commands. It's in the sidebar under Agents.\n- **API route** at `/api/clanforge` reads from the agent's data files to power the MC dashboard.\n\n**How It Works:**\n- Customers fill out the form (team name, style, game, colors, motto) and hit Generate\n- DALL-E 3 HD creates 1024x1024 logos and/or 1792x1024 banners\n- 10 styles (aggressive, minimalist, futuristic, retro, cartoon, mascot, abstract, gothic, neon, military) and 10 game categories\n- Pricing: Logo $9.99, Banner $14.99, Bundle $19.99\n- CLI also works: `node ~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/gaming-logo-gen/src/index.js generate --name \"Shadow Wolves\" --type bundle --style aggressive --game FPS`\n- Telegram commands: `/gaminglogo`, `/logo`, `/logostats`\n\n**What You Need To Do:**\n1. **Gumroad token is expired** - your `GUMROAD_ACCESS_TOKEN` in `.env` is returning 401. You'll need to re-authenticate and update the token. Once that's done, I attempted to create 3 products (Logo, Banner, Bundle) but they didn't persist due to the auth issue.\n2. **Set up payment processing** - connect Stripe or Gumroad checkout to the landing page so customers can pay before generation\n3. **Expose publicly** - the web server runs locally on port 3847. To monetize, you'll need to either deploy it (Vercel, Railway) or tunnel it (ngrok, Cloudflare Tunnel)\n4. **Create sample designs** - generate a few showcase logos to use as social proof on the landing page\n\nThe total DALL-E 3 cost per generation is ~$0.04-0.08 per image, so margins are excellent at $10-20 per sale.",
      "labels": [
        "passive-income",
        "digital-products"
      ],
