    {
      "_id": "card_1773284102000",
      "title": "Figure out blog post image strategy for Masterminds HQ",
      "description": "We need a reliable way to get cover images into Wix blog posts via API.\n\n**Problem:** Unsure if Wix API supports image uploads for blog posts.\n\n**Research needed:**\n- Check Wix Blog API docs for image/media upload endpoints\n- If not supported, explore creative workarounds:\n  - Host images elsewhere (Dropbox, S3, Imgur, GitHub) and reference by URL\n  - Use Wix Media Manager API to upload first, then reference in blog post\n  - Pre-upload images to Wix media gallery, then attach to posts\n- Find the simplest, most automatable approach\n\n**Goal:** A repeatable method to include cover images in every blog post we publish through the pipeline.\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-12 12:07)\nHere's what I did and what you need to know:\n\n---\n\n**What I built:**\n\nI researched the Wix Blog API thoroughly and found that it fully supports cover images via the `coverMedia` field — but your existing code had two bugs preventing it from working. I fixed those and built out the complete image pipeline.\n\n**Bug fixes (2 critical issues):**\n- `blog.js` was setting `draftPost.media` instead of `draftPost.coverMedia` — Wix ignores the wrong field name silently\n- `publisher.js` was building the media object as `{ wixMedia: { image: fileId } }` instead of the correct `{ enabled: true, displayed: true, custom: true, image: { id: fileId } }`\n\n**New module — `cover-image.js`:**\nCreated a cover image sourcer that uses the Pexels API to find relevant stock photos based on each blog post's title and content pillar. It searches for landscape images (1200x628 — optimal for blog covers and social cards), imports them into a \"Blog Covers\" folder in Wix Media Manager, and stores the URL in the database.\n\n**Pipeline integration:**\n- `generate-blogs.sh` now auto-fetches cover images for every new post after generation\n- The publisher already had image import logic (just wasn't working due to the bugs above) — now it correctly attaches covers when publishing\n- SEO tags (`og:image`, `twitter:image`) were already wired up to `cover_image_url`\n\n**New CLI commands added to the Wix agent:**\n- `cover-search \"query\"` — preview what Pexels returns\n- `cover-set <postId>` — find and set a cover for one post\n- `cover-backfill 10` — batch-fill covers for posts missing them\n\n**One thing you need to do:**\nGet a free Pexels API key at https://www.pexels.com/api/ and add it to `~/.openclaw/workspace/.env` as `PEXELS_API_KEY=your_key`. Takes 30 seconds — then the whole pipeline works automatically.\n\nhere is plexi Api Key.\noIAHanK9uVfPGhNeqTCqXfWwtSxZOlYIRORstk219y0DRw5y5CluOyqt",
      "labels": [
        "mastermind",
        "wix",
        "blog"
      ],
      "priority": "Med",
      "column": "doing",
      "order": 0,
      "createdAt": 1773284103007,
      "updatedAt": 1773352027954,
      "executorStatus": "completed"
    },
